column1: SIT2 || Telesales || ARMT323473 || Facing "An error was encountered while invoking KIAS-GetCustomerBAN WS." issue
column32:
Hi OGW Team

We are trying to submit a Mobile New Acq order in telesales channel on SIT2 env for *ARMT323473* .

But we are getting the following issue while triggering the Completed-Success setorderstatus via SOAP:

 

*ErrorDescription=An error was encountered while invoking KIAS-GetCustomerBAN WS. Details [Error_Code: EAI002337, Error_Message: XML Schema Validation Error, Error_Type: Validation, Error_Sevirity: E, Error_Information: : validation error: data "BIC_0" does not match regular expression "[A-Z]\{6,6}[A-Z2-9][A-NP-Z0-9]([A-Z0-9]\{3,3})\{0,1}"   (\{com.tibco.xml.validation}SIMPLE_E_REGULAR_EXPRESSION_MISMATCH) at /Result[1]/\{http://www.vodafone.de/ESB/Service/EAI/Customer/CustomerAccount/CustomerAccount-007}GetMFCustomerBANResponse[1]/\{http://www.vodafone.de/ESB/Service/EAI/Customer/CustomerAccount/CustomerAccount-007}customerDetails[1]/\{http://www.vodafone.de/ESB/Schema/EAI/Customer/MFCustomer/MFCustomerTypes-EAI-007}bankDetails[1]/\{http://www.vodafone.de/ESB/Schema/EAI/Customer/MFCustomer/MFCustomerTypes-EAI-007}bankAccountDetails[1]/\{http://www.vodafone.de/ESB/Schema/EAI/Customer/MFCustomer/MFCustomerTypes-EAI-007}BIC[1]*

*com.tibco.xml.validation.exception.ValueParseException: data "BIC_0" does not match regular expression "[A-Z]\{6,6}[A-Z2-9][A-NP-Z0-9]([A-Z0-9]\{3,3})\{0,1}"*

               *]*

 

Steps to reproduce:
 # Login to Telesales channel.
 # Add Mobile Package.
 # Select HW, tariff.
 # Click on Zum checkout.
 # Fill all the necessary details.
 # Validate IBAN.
 # Generate the contract summary.
 # Submit the order.
 # Verify our Sub is activated in KIAS.
 # Trigger Completed success status via SOAPUI.

 

Expected Result: Order should submit successfully.

Actual Result: Order is getting failed with error: *An error was encountered while invoking KIAS-GetCustomerBAN WS. Details [Error_Code: EAI002337, Error_Message: XML Schema Validation Error,* 

 **

column1: SIT1 | Retail | BAN attribute is missing in the GetSimDetails response
column32:
We are testing GetSimDetails service in SIT1 and we can receive the response from EAI.

However, as per OGW US https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-63252,  BAN attribute is also expected in the GetSimDetails response, which will then be forwarded to Omnius.

Omnius will save the BAN in its database and include it in the Submit order xml.

PFA logs for your reference.

 

Additionally, we are seeing BAN under SubsidaryCode in the GetSimDetails response. 
Omnius, however, expects a distinct attribute for BAN.

Y/N are correct values in MMC. According KIAS Spec in MMO the value ‘N’ was never valid values (since 2016), see attached values.

 
|ADVERTISING_IND|C(1)|CUSTOMER.‌ADVERTISING_IND|+MMC:+
Y / N
+MMO:+

column1: SIT1 | Legitimation section is not working as expected
column32:
We tried running one Retail prepaid new ACQ scenario in SIT1 but seems like legitimation section is not working as expected.

Could you please check?

 

User Story: https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-63385

*Steps to reproduce:*

 
 # Login to retail channel
 # Selectr prepaid package
 # Add blister and tariff
 # Move to checkout
 # Fill all the required details
 # Provide the legitimation details

*Please find my observation as below:*

**
|Sr. No.|Expectation as per user story *OS-63385*|Observation|
|1|The _Weiter_ button remained disabled until all mandatory fields were entered including the Legitimation Section. 
 ** |However, Weiter is enabled to click on even if we don’t have any of the fields from legitimation section is filled.
 ** |
|2|*Geburtsdatum (Birth Date)* should be prefilled as a non-editable, greyed-out field populated from the Kundennamen section.
 ** |However, agent is getting an option to fill the DOB again in the _Legitimation_ section.
 ** |
|3|*Ausweis-Nr. (ID Number)* field should be ** Enabled only after selecting a value in the ID Type drop-down.
 ** |However, this field is enabled without selecting any value from ID Type drop-down.
 ** |
|4|*Ausweis-Nr. (ID Number):* Validation must be like Kundenidentifikation from postpaid checkout for a German passport and German ID card for ID type dt. Personalausweis &
dt. Reisepass for other ID Types no field validation is needed.
 ** |However, no validation is being performed for even after selecting ID type dt. Personalausweis & dt. Reisepass 
 ** |
|5|*Ausgegeben am (Issued On):* The agent should be offered the calendar option to select the date Validated that the date was not in the future.
 ** | * However, agent is getting an option to select the date from Future only, there is no option available to select the date from past, it seems to be disabled.
 * Even after selecting date from future, we are not getting any warning message or pop up.

 ** |
|6|*Gültig bis (Valid Until):* The agent was offered the calendar option to select the date, ensuring the date was greater than or equal to the current date.
 ** | * However, we are not getting an option to select the date from current date or month.
 * There is only option to select the date from next month or after that.

 ** |
|7|*Nummer elektron. Aufenthaltstitel (Electronic Residence Permit Number)* field should be enabled only if the ID Type was "ausl. Reisepass mit eAT."
 ** |However, Nummer elektron. Aufenthaltstitel ** field is enabled irrespective of the ID Type we are selecting.
 ** |
|8|*Elektron. Aufenthaltstitel gültig bis (Electronic Residence Permit Valid Until)* field should be enabled only if the ID Type was "ausl. Reisepass mit eAT." And should accepted dates greater than or equal to the current date.
 ** | * However, *Elektron. Aufenthaltstitel gültig bis* field is enabled irrespective of the ID type we are selecting.
 * Also, ** we are not getting an option to select the date from current date or month.
 * There is only option to select the date from next month or after that.

 |
|9|*Legitimierung bestätigt (Legitimacy Confirmed)* Checkbox should be enabled only when all mandatory fields were entered or pre-filled and should remain disabled if fields were incomplete or skipped.
 ** |However, Legitimierung bestätigt checkbox is enabled even if we are not selecting any of the fields from Legitimation section.
 |
